    Setup biological inputs for estimation model

    Setup_Mod_Biologicals.Rd

    Setup biological inputs for estimation model

    Setup_Mod_Biologicals(
  input_list,
  WAA,
  MatAA,
  AgeingError = NULL,
  Use_M_prior = 0,
  M_prior = NA,
  fit_lengths = 0,
  SizeAgeTrans = NA,
  M_spec = NULL,
  ...
)

    Arguments

    input_list

    List containing a data list, parameter list, and map list

    WAA

    Inputs of weight at age dimensioned by n_region, n_year, n_ages, n_sexes

    MatAA

    Inputs of maturity at age dimensioned by n_region, n_year, n_ages, n_sexes

    AgeingError

    Inputs of ageing error matrix dimensioned by n_ages, n_ages. Default behavior uses an identity matrix (no ageing error)

    Use_M_prior

    Whether or not to use natural mortality prior, == 0 don't use, == 1 use

    M_prior

    Vector of natural mortality priors with the first element representing the mean in normal space, and the second element representing the sd.

    fit_lengths

    Whether or not to fit length data, == 0 dont fit, == 1 fit

    SizeAgeTrans

    Size age transition matrix dimensioned by n_regions, n_years, n_lens, n_ages, n_sexes

    M_spec

    Character specifying options for how to estimate natural mortality. Default is NULL such that it is estimated for 2 sexes or only estimated for a single sex if it is a single sex model. Other options include "est_shared_s" which estimates the same natural mortality rate if n_sexes == 2. The other option is "fix" which fixes all natural mortality parameters.

    ...

    Parameter starting values for ln_M and M_offset if not using default
